In New Zealand where testing is undertaken by a third party testing provider, full records including test values of all tests performed should be kept with the following information included, where relevant, as a minimum:
a)	Earth continuity resistance;
b)	Insulation resistance;
c)	Leakage current;
d)	Visual inspection.
NOTE â€“
(1)	Other records may be required for specific equipment; e.g. a record of polarity may be required on equipment with rewireable plugs, sockets or fittings.
(2)	Electronic records are acceptable.
